HEADWORD: Skep
<hw>Skep</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel. <ets>skeppa</ets>
a measure, bushel; cf. Gael. <ets>sgeap</ets> a basket, a
beehive.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A coarse round farm basket.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Tusser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A beehive.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skeptic</ent>⟦br⟧
